meta {
  name: POST climatisation start (rich, v2.10.0)
  type: http
  seq: 24
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/vehicle/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/climatisation/start
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
  Accept: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "targetTemperatureInCelsius": 21.5,
    "windowHeatingEnabled": true,
    "zoneFrontLeftEnabled": true,
    "zoneFrontRightEnabled": true,
    "zoneRearLeftEnabled": false,
    "zoneRearRightEnabled": false,
    "climatisationAtUnlock": true,
    "climatisationMode": "comfort"
  }
}

docs {
  v2.10.0. Rich climate-start payload for the CARIAD BFF. Same
  /climatisation/start endpoint as the separate-endpoint fallback in
  06_POST_climatisation_start.bru, but with the full optional body:
  per-seat heating zones, glass / window heating, at-unlock continuation
  and climatisation mode (comfort or economy).

  Each body key is optional. Omitting a key keeps the brand-backend
  default; partial submissions are accepted, but seat heating is
  treated as a group: once any zone is present, all four zone keys
  must be sent so the backend has a coherent zone configuration.

  Exposed in HA via the new ``vag_connect.start_climate_control``
  service (device-selector based, falls back to basic start for
  non-CARIAD brands at the coordinator level).

  Implementation:
    - VWEUClient.command_start_climate_control() in
      cariad/api/vw_eu.py (Audi inherits via AudiClient(VWEUClient)).
    - Coordinator.async_start_climate_control() routes Audi + VW
      brands to the rich payload, other brands to async_start_climatisation.
}
